{"links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-math/pullrequests/263/comments/63417336.json"}, "code": {"href": "https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-math/diff/ignitionrobotics/ign-math:a47a89275434..381d3b5327c9?path=include%2Fignition%2Fmath%2FMaterial.hh"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-math/pull-requests/263/_/diff#comment-63417336"}}, "parent": {"id": 63414719, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-math/pullrequests/263/comments/63414719.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-math/pull-requests/263/_/diff#comment-63414719"}}}, "deleted": false, "pullrequest": {"type": "pullrequest", "id": 263, "links": {"self": {"href": "data/repositories/ignitionrobotics/ign-math/pullrequests/263.json"}, "html": {"href": "#!/ignitionrobotics/ign-math/pull-requests/263"}}, "title": "Material density constructor"}, "content": {"raw": "Maybe I misunderstand the motivation for not naming this class `MaterialDensity`.\n\nThe same effect could be achieved as follows, is that not enough?\n\n~~~\nMaterial mat();\nmat->SetDensity(1.0);\n~~~\n\nIf we can foresee that a constructor will eventually be deprecated, I think it's better not to even implement it in the first place, right? Deprecation cycles are costly for downstream users.", "markup": "markdown", "html": "<p>Maybe I misunderstand the motivation for not naming this class <code>MaterialDensity</code>.</p>\n<p>The same effect could be achieved as follows, is that not enough?</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\"><pre><span></span>Material mat();\nmat-&gt;SetDensity(1.0);\n</pre></div>\n\n\n<p>If we can foresee that a constructor will eventually be deprecated, I think it's better not to even implement it in the first place, right? Deprecation cycles are costly for downstream users.</p>", "type": "rendered"}, "created_on": "2018-05-04T16:20:04.822262+00:00", "user": {"display_name": "Louise Poubel", "uuid": "{5cfa2075-477b-4ded-bdb9-8d24795